 is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Reade was born in 1278, in Carmarthen, Carmarthenshire, Wales, his father, John Reade, was 30 and his mother, Joan Ludlow, was 30. He married Jane Arblasted in 1304, in Carmarthen, Carmarthenshire, Wales. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died in 1370, in Pembroke, Pembrokeshire, Wales, at the age of 92."},"et":{"1278–1370":"1278–1370","1278–Male":"1278–Surnud","1272–1360":"1272–1360","1304–1388":"1304–1388","1295–Male":"1295–Surnud","1248–Male":"1248–Surnud","1248–1348":"1248–1348","1304":"1304","1348":"1348","1248":"1248","1278":"1278","1388":"1388","1295":"1295","from 1295 to 1320":"1295 kuni 1320","1360":"1360","1272":"1272","1370":"1370","Carmarthen, Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Carmarthen, Carmarthenshire, Wales","Wales, United Kingdom":"Wales, United Kingdom","Wales":"Wales","Pembroke, Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Pembroke, Pembrokeshire, Wales"},"fi":{"1278–1370":"1278–1370","1278–Male":"1278–Kuollut","1272–1360":"1272–1360","1304–1388":"1304–1388","1295–Male":"1295–Kuollut","1248–Male":"1248–Kuollut","1248–1348":"1248–1348","1304":"1304","1348":"1348","1248":"1248","1278":"1278","1388":"1388","1295":"1295","from 1295 to 1320":"vuodesta 1295 vuoteen 1320","1360":"1360","1272":"1272","1370":"1370","Carmarthen, Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Carmarthen, Carmarthenshire, Wales","Wales, United Kingdom":"Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Wales":"Wales","Pembroke, Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Pembroke, Pembrokeshire, Wales"},"fr":{"1278–1370":"1278–13